    "chapter": {
        "bookTitle": "Proverbs",
        "delineation": "Chapter",
        "number": 11,
        "summary": "The state and rewards of the righteous and the wicked are contrasted\u2014When a wicked man dies, his expectations perish\u2014He who wins souls is wise.",
        "chapterAugmentations": [],
        "verses": [
            {
                "text": "A false balance is abomination to the Lord: but a just weight is his delight.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "OR\u00a0Deceptive scales (i.e., made to deceive).",
                        "start": 0,
                        "end": 1
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Amos 8:5.",
                        "start": 8,
                        "end": 15
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 16,
                        "end": 18
                    },
                    {
                        "start": 62,
                        "end": 64
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "When pride cometh, then cometh shame: but with the lowly is wisdom.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "2\u00a0Ne. 26:20 (20\u201322); D&C 38:39.",
                        "start": 5,
                        "end": 10
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Shame.",
                        "start": 31,
                        "end": 36
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 0,
                        "end": 4
                    },
                    {
                        "start": 57,
                        "end": 59
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "The integrity of the upright shall guide them: but the perverseness of transgressors shall destroy them.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Integrity.",
                        "start": 4,
                        "end": 13
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "Riches profit not in the day of wrath: but righteousness delivereth from death.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Treasure.",
                        "start": 0,
                        "end": 6
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "D&C 1:9 (8\u201310).",
                        "start": 32,
                        "end": 37
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "The righteousness of the perfect shall direct his way: but the wicked shall fall by his own wickedness.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Prov. 13:6.",
                        "start": 4,
                        "end": 17
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Esth. 7:9.",
                        "start": 76,
                        "end": 80
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "The righteousness of the upright shall deliver them: but transgressors shall be taken in their own naughtiness.",
                "footnotes": [],
                "associatedContents": [
                    {
                        "type": "paper-page-number",
                        "data": 822
                    }
                ],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 89,
                        "end": 98
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "When a wicked man dieth, his expectation shall perish: and the hope of unjust men perisheth.",
                "footnotes": [],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 25,
                        "end": 28
                    },
                    {
                        "start": 78,
                        "end": 81
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "The righteous is delivered out of trouble, and the wicked cometh in his stead.",
                "footnotes": [],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "An hypocrite with his mouth destroyeth his neighbour: but through knowledge shall the just be delivered.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "D&C 50:7 (7\u20138).",
                        "start": 3,
                        "end": 12
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "D&C 51:19.",
                        "start": 86,
                        "end": 90
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 18,
                        "end": 21
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "When it goeth well with the righteous, the city rejoiceth: and when the wicked perish, there is shouting.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Prov. 28:12.",
                        "start": 28,
                        "end": 37
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 87,
                        "end": 95
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "By the blessing of the upright the city is exalted: but it is overthrown by the mouth of the wicked.",
                "footnotes": [],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "He that is void of wisdom despiseth his neighbour: but a man of understanding holdeth his peace.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "D&C 59:6.",
                        "start": 40,
                        "end": 49
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "A talebearer revealeth secrets: but he that is of a faithful spirit concealeth the matter.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Gossip.",
                        "start": 2,
                        "end": 12
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "Where no counsel is, the people fall: but in the multitude of counsellors there is safety.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Counsel.",
                        "start": 9,
                        "end": 16
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Prov. 24:6.",
                        "start": 49,
                        "end": 58
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Counselor.",
                        "start": 62,
                        "end": 73
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 17,
                        "end": 20
                    },
                    {
                        "start": 74,
                        "end": 82
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "He that is surety for a stranger shall smart for it: and he that hateth suretiship is sure.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Prov. 6:1; 22:26.",
                        "start": 11,
                        "end": 17
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 45,
                        "end": 52
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "A gracious woman retaineth honour: and strong men retain riches.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Woman.",
                        "start": 11,
                        "end": 16
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 46,
                        "end": 49
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "The merciful man doeth good to his own soul: but he that is cruel troubleth his own flesh.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Cruelty.",
                        "start": 60,
                        "end": 65
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 49,
                        "end": 59
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "The wicked worketh a deceitful work: but to him that soweth righteousness shall be a sure reward.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Deceit.",
                        "start": 21,
                        "end": 30
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Righteousness.",
                        "start": 60,
                        "end": 73
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Reward; Wages.",
                        "start": 90,
                        "end": 96
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 74,
                        "end": 82
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "As righteousness tendeth to life: so he that pursueth evil pursueth it to his own death.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Prov. 19:23; 2\u00a0Ne. 9:39.",
                        "start": 28,
                        "end": 32
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 17,
                        "end": 24
                    },
                    {
                        "start": 59,
                        "end": 70
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "They that are of a froward heart are abomination to the Lord: but such as are upright in their way are his delight.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Prov. 21:8.",
                        "start": 14,
                        "end": 16
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Ps. 101:4.",
                        "start": 19,
                        "end": 26
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 33,
                        "end": 36
                    },
                    {
                        "start": 66,
                        "end": 77
                    },
                    {
                        "start": 89,
                        "end": 94
                    },
                    {
                        "start": 99,
                        "end": 102
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "Though hand join in hand, the wicked shall not be unpunished: but the seed of the righteous shall be delivered.",
                "footnotes": [],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 0,
                        "end": 6
                    },
                    {
                        "start": 12,
                        "end": 16
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "As a jewel of gold in a swine's snout, so is a fair woman which is without discretion.",
                "footnotes": [],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 0,
                        "end": 2
                    },
                    {
                        "start": 39,
                        "end": 44
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "The desire of the righteous is only good: but the expectation of the wicked is wrath.",
                "footnotes": [],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 28,
                        "end": 30
                    },
                    {
                        "start": 42,
                        "end": 45
                    },
                    {
                        "start": 76,
                        "end": 78
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "There is that scattereth, and yet increaseth; and there is that withholdeth more than is meet, but it tendeth to poverty.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Prov. 13:7.",
                        "start": 34,
                        "end": 44
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 50,
                        "end": 58
                    },
                    {
                        "start": 99,
                        "end": 109
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "The liberal soul shall be made fat: and he that watereth shall be watered also himself.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Matt. 7:2.",
                        "start": 48,
                        "end": 56
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "He that withholdeth corn, the people shall curse him: but blessing shall be upon the head of him that selleth it.",
                "footnotes": [],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 67,
                        "end": 75
                    },
                    {
                        "start": 110,
                        "end": 113
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "He that diligently seeketh good procureth favour: but he that seeketh mischief, it shall come unto him.",
                "footnotes": [],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "He that trusteth in his riches shall fall: but the righteous shall flourish as a branch.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Trustworthiness.",
                        "start": 8,
                        "end": 16
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "He that troubleth his own house shall inherit the wind: and the fool shall be servant to the wise of heart.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Marriage, Fatherhood.",
                        "start": 26,
                        "end": 31
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 69,
                        "end": 77
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "The fruit of the righteous is a tree of life; and he that winneth souls is wise.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "1\u00a0Ne. 11:25.",
                        "start": 32,
                        "end": 44
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 27,
                        "end": 29
                    },
                    {
                        "start": 72,
                        "end": 74
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "Behold, the righteous shall be recompensed in the earth: much more the wicked and the sinner.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "D&C 1:10; 56:19.",
                        "start": 31,
                        "end": 42
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            }
        ]
    }
}